00:12:10,015 --> 00:12:14,282
Where they've shown that in the brain, in these...

107
00:12:14,532 --> 00:12:42,260
I can't recall anyway in the circuit they show that actually a decision has been made and then the person becomes aware does it and then thinks that they've actually made the decision but the decision was actually made before they became aware of it yeah now that is a simple pure wonderful example of the unaware life that is the deluded life

108
00:12:42,865 --> 00:12:47,210
where you think you're making the decisions, but actually you're being an automaton.

109
00:12:47,230 --> 00:12:50,192
You're actually running according to past habits.

110
00:12:50,894 --> 00:12:59,323
Now, the whole point is that as you become aware of those intentions, then they don't get empowered.

111
00:13:00,245 --> 00:13:03,548
You see the intention coming up, like we did, intending to sit.

112
00:13:04,149 --> 00:13:09,075
If you're there still, you see, with that awareness, and you see that intention to sit coming up,

113
00:13:09,510 --> 00:13:15,917
There's a moment there where you can say, well, should I be sitting or should I be walking or should I be doing something else?

114
00:13:16,357 --> 00:13:16,538
See?

115
00:13:16,998 --> 00:13:18,700
That's how you take control of your life.

116
00:13:20,120 --> 00:13:24,725
How many times has suddenly you've said to yourself, oh, I'll have a cup of coffee.

117
00:13:25,567 --> 00:13:26,788
